                                                <section>
                                                    <h2>HOW BLOOMINGDALE'S WORKS WITH MENTORING USA AND HELP USA</h2>
                                                    <p>HELP USA is a national housing and homeless services organization dedicated to the premise that all people deserve safe, stable housing. Mentoring USA, an affiliate of HELP USA, is a New York City–based nonprofit providing structured, site-based mentoring to children ages 7–21.</p>
                                                    <p>Bloomingdale's has been a proud partner of both HELP USA and Mentoring USA since 1998, supporting each organization through fundraising activities, employee volunteerism and direct donations. Bloomingdale's employees are active in the donating of goods and providing of volunteer services to HELP USA, including Hurricane Sandy relief efforts in 2012. Since partnering with Mentoring USA, Bloomingdale's mentors have volunteered their time to serve over 1,000 children nationally and we remain Mentoring USA's largest corporate partner. Together we highlight the Bloomingdale's belief that all children deserve an equal chance at success.</p>
                                                </section>
